2026-05-11T19:09:41.8961536Z [36;1mcat >user.bazelrc <<EOF[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8962373Z [36;1m# Disable the local disk cache as we use a remote cache and don't want[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8963430Z [36;1m# two copies of every output taking up disk space. The only way to[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8964365Z [36;1m# disable the disk cache is with an empty string:[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8965226Z [36;1m# https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/5308[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8965968Z [36;1mbuild --disk_cache=[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8966813Z [36;1m[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8967417Z [36;1m# Enable remote cache for our CI but minimize downloads.[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8968564Z [36;1mbuild --remote_cache=https://storage.googleapis.com/carbon-builds-github-v${CACHE_VERSION}[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8969663Z [36;1mbuild --remote_download_outputs=minimal[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8970331Z [36;1m[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8971239Z [36;1m# Allow passing targets that are incompatible so that our explicit[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8972306Z [36;1m# target lists work more like //... wild card patterns in CI. In CI,[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8982047Z [36;1m# we're using explicit target lists to prune to a minimal set of[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8983181Z [36;1m# dependencies, and so skipping incompatible targets is the expected[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8984086Z [36;1m# behavior.[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8984719Z [36;1mbuild --skip_incompatible_explicit_targets[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8985434Z [36;1m[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8986130Z [36;1m# We import a special key into every action in order to key the Bazel[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8987181Z [36;1m# remote cache in a way that avoids collisions between different[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8988250Z [36;1m# runners. Anything that might change the system external to Bazel but[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8989363Z [36;1m# not be fully captured by the sand-boxing of the build should be used[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8990425Z [36;1m# as part of the key. We don't need to use the CPU target for example,[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8991665Z [36;1m# as that is captured by Bazel's configuration of each action. And the[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8992722Z [36;1m# Clang version is incorporated by our Clang toolchain setup. But we[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8993752Z [36;1m# do need to capture any differences between GitHub runner OSes that[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8994770Z [36;1m# don't impact the Bazel configuration to avoid collisions between[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8995586Z [36;1m# those.[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8996339Z [36;1mbuild --action_env=BAZEL_REMOTE_CACHE_KEY=github-action-ubuntu-22.04[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8997203Z [36;1m[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8997879Z [36;1mbuild --google_credentials=/home/runner/remote_cache_key.json[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8998713Z [36;1m[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.8999418Z [36;1m# Set an artificially high jobs count. This flag controls the number[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9000497Z [36;1m# of concurrency Bazel itself uses, which is essential for actions[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9002034Z [36;1m# that are internally blocked on for example downloading results form[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9003146Z [36;1m# the cache above. Without setting this high, Bazel will pick a small[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9004203Z [36;1m# number based on the available host CPUs and the reality will be a[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9005288Z [36;1m# long chain of largely serialized download events with little or no[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9006204Z [36;1m# usage of the host machine. Fortunately, local actions are[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9006789Z [36;1m# *separately* gated on '--local_*_resources' that will avoid a large[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9007392Z [36;1m# jobs value overwhelming the host. There is a bug to make downloads[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9007989Z [36;1m# behave completely asynchronously and remove the need for this filed[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9008522Z [36;1m# back in 2018 but work seemed to not finish:[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9008993Z [36;1m# https://github.com/bazelbuild/bazel/issues/6394[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9009418Z [36;1m#[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9009828Z [36;1m# There is a new effort (yay!) but until then it seems worth using the[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9010413Z [36;1m# workaround of a high jobs value. The biggest downside (increased[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9011234Z [36;1m# heap usage) seems like it isn't currently a big loss for our builds.[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9011721Z [36;1m#[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9012114Z [36;1m# Higher values like 50 have led to CI failures with network errors[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9012804Z [36;1m# and IOExceptions, see[0m
2026-05-11T19:09:41.9013321Z [36;1m# https://discord.com/channels/655572317891461132/707150492370862090/1151605725576056934[0m
